The Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from fraudsters who replace the bank’s phone number has increased.
This is reported by Kommersant with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator transmitted to the telecom operators information about more than 2.5 thousand numbers, from which customers of various financial organizations were called.
In 189 cases, the operators found a replacement number.
A further 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases a restriction on the use of financial services was imposed.
Artem Sychev, deputy head of the information security department of the Central Bank, said that a wide range of Russian banks were faced with the replacement of the number.
He explained that the operators do not always respond to the Central Bank’s warnings about fraudulent calls, citing the absence of such an obligation in the law “On Communications”.
In the Bank "Open", Rosbank and Alfa-Bank confirmed information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with the replacement number.
As reported in the press service of Bilaina, some of the information about fraudulent calls that the Central Bank transmitted was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are actually used by banks to communicate with customers.
Blocking them would lead to failures in the work of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of scammers numbers, which the operator will contact with each call to verify the number.
He explained that such a framework would require amendments to the legislation.
