Currently, the participants of the action, replacing each other, stand, holding a poster with the inscription "Freedom for all" and the names of those convicted and arrested after the non-agreed rallies in Moscow in the summer of 2019.
In addition to Ustinov, on the poster names Egor Zhukov, Kirill Zhukov, Danil Beglets, Evgeny Kovalenko, Konstantin Kotov, Ivan Podkopayev, Aidar Gubaidulin, Alexei Minyailo, Sergey Fomin, Samariddin Rajabova, Nikita Chirkova
On September 16, the Tver court of Moscow sentenced 24-year-old Ustinov to 3.5 years of a colony of the general regime on charges of using violence against a fighter of OMON Rosgvardia at a non-agreed action on August 3 in the center of Moscow (Article 2, Article 318 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation).
After that, on September 20, at the request of the Prosecutor General's Office, the court changed Ustin's measure of restraint from detention to a non-departure subscription.
Thus, the petition for the release of Ustinov received more than 112,000 signatures in a day.
Theatre and film artists started a flashmob in support of their colleagues.
To participate in a single picket in solidarity with the actor on September 18 in the Old Square, the turn was built.
The review of the case was demanded by human rights defenders, journalists, scientists, teachers, doctors, Orthodox priests.
As reported to "Interfax" sister Ustinov Yulia, at a meeting on September 29 in the capital in support of the figures of the "Moscow case" her brother does not plan to speak.
Deliveries of "sanctions" to Russia fell by 100 times
The government of the Russian Federation estimated that the supply of agricultural products and food to Russia from the countries that fell under the Russian food embargo has decreased more than 100 times since 2013.
According to a report sent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31 thousand tons of products were imported from sanctioning countries against 3 million 442.2 thousand tons for the same period of 2013, reports Interfax.
At the same time, the value of imported products decreased to $226.5 million from $4 billion to 975.5 million, respectively.
We are talking about the supply of goods that did not fall under the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the fallen volumes of prohibited imports were compensated by an increase in imports from the CIS countries, Africa, Southeast Asia, Serbia.
At the end of August, the government extended until December 31, 2020 the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and food, which are prohibited to import into Russia under counter-sanctions.
The document, posted on the official legal information portal, noted that the period of validity of the rules was extended by another one for a year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the decision to abolish the sanction applied to products from the United States, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, from August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein joined this list, from January 1, 2016 - Ukraine.
The decree signed by Putin on the destruction of illegally imported “sanctions” (products that fell under the food embargo that Moscow imposed in response to anti-Russian sanctions of the West) entered into force in 2015.
In turn, the government has authorized the destruction of “sanctioned” food in any lawful way.
As Western sanctions continue, Russia has also extended its retaliatory measures.
At the same time, the products that citizens import for personal use, this measure does not apply.
The ban does not apply to the import of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Council under the President of the Russian Federation on the development of civil society and human rights, Mikhail Fedotov, previously called the destruction of food "just immoral", and this, according to him, negatively affects the education of people.
Moreover, with the initiative to prohibit the destruction of food suitable for consumption, at the beginning of June, Rospotrebnadzor spoke.
After that, a similar recommendation to the government was given by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And Deputy Prime Minister Alexei Gordeev said that destroying food products is wrong, and it is necessary to think about how you can use them for their intended purpose, assessing the quality.
The head of the company is found guilty of tax evasion
By the sentence of the Leninsky District Court of Cheboksary the director of the LLC "Land and Law" Vyacheslav Morozov is guilty of the crime provided for in part 2 of Article 199 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (avoidance from paying taxes from the organization by including in the tax declaration is known to be false).
This is reported by the press service of the investigative department of the SKR on Chuvashi.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov entered information about incomplete transactions in the tax accounting documents of the LLC.
According to the fictitious documents, the company bore additional costs, and therefore, the amount of taxes to be paid for the added value and for the profit of the organization was reduced by 11.2 million rubles.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years in prison.
By 2023, the first school of a new format will open in the center of the capital
A new school will be opened in Khamovniki.
According to the head of Moskomstroyinvest, Anastasia Pyatova, there will create all the conditions for self-realization and development of children’s talents.
The educational institution decided to call the "New Look".
This project will be supervised by the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia and the Foundation "Economic Development of the Higher School".
The design of the building with an area of about 10 thousand "squares" is planned to begin next year.
They will complete the construction at the end of 2022, and the next will begin to recruit the first students.
"The project envisages the creation of a public, non-commercial educational space, which will be based on the traditions of the classical Moscow school and experimental methods," the press service of Moskomstroyinvest said.
In Chile began to build a telescope worth 1 billion euros
This is reported by TASS with reference to the press service of the European Southern Observatory (ESO).
The European Extremely Large Telescope (E-ELT), the most expensive and ambitious ground-based astronomical project yet, has officially begun construction of the dome of the building this week, according to ESO.
Its total value is estimated by ESO to exceed one billion euros.
Much of this money will be spent on manufacturing equipment and building an observatory building.
The most expensive and complex component of the telescope is its record-breaking large mirror, whose diameter will be about 39 meters.
It will be assembled from 798 hexagonal segments measuring 1.4 meters.
This huge mirror, as well as two auxiliary reflecting surfaces with a diameter of 4.2 and 3.75 meters, will help E-ELT get the first detailed photos of planets outside the solar system, stars in other galaxies, as well as looking for Earth's doubles.
In addition, scientists will try to use this observatory to observe the surroundings of Sgr A*, a supermassive black hole in the center of the Milky Way.
Despite the fact that the construction of the dome is just beginning, the mirrors, scientific instruments and other components of the observatory scientists, engineers and other specialists have been developing for three years - since the announcement of the first plans for the construction of the E-ELT.
The contract for the production of the main mirror, which totaled about 400 million euros, was awarded to the German company SCHOTT and the French company Safran Reosc.
